<h2>DIET PLAN</h2>
<p><strong>Breakfast:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1 cup idli/dosa with 1/2 cup sambar and coconut chutney </li>
<li>1 cup vegetable poha with nuts (almonds, walnuts)</li>
<li>1 cup oatmeal with milk and berries</li>
<li>1 cup curd with fruits (apple, banana) and nuts</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Lunch:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1 cup vegetable rice with 1/2 cup dal and 1/2 cup mixed vegetable curry</li>
<li>1 cup brown rice with 1 cup mixed vegetable curry</li>
<li>1 cup lentil soup with 1 chapati</li>
<li>1 cup vegetable salad</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Dinner:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>2 chapatis with 1/2 cup vegetable curry and 1/2 cup mixed salad</li>
<li>1 cup quinoa with 1/2 cup vegetable curry</li>
<li>1 cup vegetable soup with 1 chapati</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Snacks:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1 cup mixed nuts (almonds, walnuts)</li>
<li>1 fruit (apple, banana, orange)</li>
<li>1 cup curd with fruits and nuts</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Fluids:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Drink 2-2.5 litres of water throughout the day.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> You can adjust the portion sizes based on your individual needs and energy expenditure. Make sure to include plenty of fruits, vegetables, and nuts in your diet. Choose whole grains over refined grains. Avoid sugary drinks and processed foods.</p>
<h2>ADDITIONAL TIPS</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Diabetes Management:</strong><ul>
<li>Consult with your doctor or a registered dietitian to create a personalized diabetes management plan. </li>
<li>Monitor your blood sugar levels regularly.</li>
<li>Include low-glycemic index foods in your diet.</li>
<li>Opt for healthy fats and lean protein sources.</li>
<li>Limit processed foods, sugary beverages, and refined carbohydrates.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Peanut Allergy:</strong><ul>
<li>Strictly avoid any foods containing peanuts or peanut products.</li>
<li>Read food labels carefully.</li>
<li>Inform restaurants about your allergy when dining out.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
